1 DATE 7 May 1909
1 PLAC Lewis Ponds
1 _DSCR Captain William Reynolds in newspaper article in the Leader (Orange) 
1 _META <metadataxml><transcription>Captain William Reynolds, an old and respected resident of Lewis Ponds sold his farm and residence to Mr H Williams last week. For years the Captain successfully managed the Mt Britannia, Icely and Tom&apos;s mines. He i
2 CONC s considered one of the best authorities on copper in the district. Captain Reynolds has lived in and about this locality for almost 40 years. He is still undecided whether he will go to Bodangora (where is son resides) or remain at Lewis Ponds. I
2 CONC t is to be sincerely hoped the latter will be carried out as his departure from here would be very much regretted. Mr H. Williams is a resident of Emu Swamp and is already installed in his new home.</transcription></metadataxml>
